I'd still like to explain why a riceballtail lynch today would be a good idea. If he is scum and we overlook it because he's been quiet, then that still means there's going to be a scum running around lynching people in the nighttime. He hasn't been contributing anything worthwhile and has only been contributing to the bandwagon. If we do happen to choose the wrong person [hopefully not] his contribution will just lynch that person faster if he continues to jump on bandwagons. I don't think it's worth the risk to know that it now it takes fewer people who actually care and just have someone jump on the bandwagon to lynch someone who could be innocent. And like I already said his actions are scummy- so lynch a scum and keep townies from being wrongly lynched.

